## 🛠️ How to optimize it in your NixOS config
When you use the graphical installer, select Btrfs as your file system. Once installed, ensure your hardware-configuration.nix (or your main configuration.nix) mounts the drive with the compress=zstd flag. It will look like this:

fileSystems."/" = {
  device = "/dev/disk/by-uuid/your-uuid";
  fsType = "btrfs";
  options = [ "subvol=@" "compress=zstd" "noatime" ]; # "noatime" boosts NVMe life & speed
};

Using Btrfs with Zstd compression on a massive 2TB drive is practically free real estate for a gaming rig.

